description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEPUTY HEAD OF OPERATIONS 8b&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 posts – 1 rotate Royal Gwent Hospital(RGH) to Grange University Hospital (GUH) 1 rotate Nevill Hall Hospital (NHH) to &lt;strong&gt;Grange University Hospital (GUH)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opening of the Grange University Hospital and changes to the way we run our hospitals bring exciting opportunities for our Operational teams. As a result we have opportunities for 2 experienced operational managers who are passionate about patient flow and overarching site management to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for 2 Deputy Heads of Operations to complement the existing team. 1 post is based at Nevill Hall hospital in Abergavenny and will rotate to Grange University Hospital, the other is based in Grange University Hospital and will rotate to Royal Gwent Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced nurse leader who wants to make a difference and influence the patient’s journey through our systems?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you committed to improve the quality of care for our patients, ensuring they are in the right bed first time?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders will have specific responsibility for the leadership, management and improvement of patient flow from admission to discharge throughout the hospitals, underpinning delivery of urgent care and planned care key quality and access standards and ensuring patients are stepped up and stepped down in a safe and timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for leading the clinical/site operational team across GUH, RGH and NHH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a new challenge and want to be part of a forward thinking, dynamic team, who truly values the patient experience, we would welcome your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: Thursday, 12th November 2020 (midnight)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Potential Date of Interview: Monday 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kathryn Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Associate Director of Operations,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01633 435901 or 07969567647&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;email: Kathryn.smith2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
